-- Fourteen U.S. oil refineries shut due to Gustav: DOE
-- 
-- Tue Sep 2, 2008 11:33am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/02/us-gustav-oil-refineries-idUSWAT00996620080902

 

 WASHINGTON  (Reuters) - Fourteen oil refineries along the U.S. Gulf Coast with a combined refining capacity of 2.716 million barrels of oil per day were shut down because of Hurricane Gustav, the Energy Department said on Tuesday. 

 Another 10 refineries with a combined capacity of 3.099 million barrels a day are operating at reduced rates, the department said, based on information from oil companies and various trade press sources. (Reporting by  Tom Doggett ; Editing by Marguerita Choy)